In addition to finding the two most common letters in the first and last names of the author of "The Catcher in the Rye", modify the existing C# code to also count the number of times each of these letters appear in the author's full name. The output should display both the letters and their respective counts.

### Response:
Here's the modified C# code that counts the number of times each of the two most common letters appear in the author's full name:
```
using System;
using System.Linq;
class Program {
 static void Main() {
 string fullName = "Jerome David Salinger";
 var letterCount = fullName
 .Where(c => char.IsLetter(c))
 .GroupBy(c => c)
 .ToDictionary(g => g.Key, g => g.Count())
 .OrderByDescending(kv => kv.Value);
 Console.WriteLine("Two most common letters in first and last names:");
 string[] names = fullName.Split(' ');
 foreach (string name in names) {
 var mostCommonLetters = name
 .Where(c => char.IsLetter(c))
 .GroupBy(c => c)
 .ToDictionary(g => g.Key, g => g.Count())
 .OrderByDescending(kv => kv.Value)
 .Take(2);
 foreach (var kv in mostCommonLetters) {
 Console.WriteLine($"{kv.Key}: {kv.Value} times in {name}");
 }
 }
