How can I use C# to write a program that converts any sentence in the present tense to future tense? Can you provide a sample code that takes in a user input sentence and outputs the same sentence in the future tense?

### Response:
Yes, I can help you with that. Here's a sample code that takes in a user input sentence and outputs the same sentence in the future tense:
```csharp
using System;
class Program
{
 static void Main(string[] args)
 {
 Console.WriteLine("Enter a sentence in present tense:");
 string sentence = Console.ReadLine();
 // split the sentence into words
 string[] words = sentence.Split(' ');
 // loop through each word and convert to future tense if it's a verb
 for (int i = 0; i < words.Length; i++)
 {
 if (words[i].EndsWith("s") || words[i].EndsWith("es"))
 {
 // present simple tense (e.g. walks, eats)
 words[i] = words[i].Substring(0, words[i].Length - 1) + "will";
 }
 else if (words[i].EndsWith("ing"))
 {
 // present continuous tense (e.g. walking, eating)
 words[i] = words[i].Substring(0, words[i].Length - 3) + "will be " + words[i].Substring(0, words[i].Length - 3) + "ing";
 }
 }
 // join the words back into a sentence
 string futureSentence = string.Join(" ", words);
 Console.WriteLine("The sentence in future tense is:");
 Console.WriteLine(futureSentence);
 }
}
```
This code splits the input sentence into words, loops through each word, and converts it to future tense if it's a verb. It then joins the words back into a sentence and outputs it to the console. Note that this code only handles simple present tense and present continuous tense verbs, and may not work correctly for other tenses.

