Can you show me an example of converting temperature readings between Fahrenheit and Celsius using PHP with XML data format? Additionally, can you provide the code for converting 82 degrees Fahrenheit to Celsius and 28 degrees Celsius to Fahrenheit using XML data format?

### Response:
Certainly! Here's an example code for converting temperature readings between Fahrenheit and Celsius using PHP with XML data format:
```
php
// Define the conversion functions
function fahrenheit_to_celsius($fahrenheit) {
 $celsius = ($fahrenheit - 32) * 5/9;
 return $celsius;
}
function celsius_to_fahrenheit($celsius) {
 $fahrenheit = ($celsius * 9/5) + 32;
 return $fahrenheit;
}
// Create the XML document
$xml = new SimpleXMLElement('<temperatures/');
// Add the Fahrenheit temperature
$fahrenheit = 82;
$celsius = fahrenheit_to_celsius($fahrenheit);
$temp = $xml->addChild('temperature');
$temp->addChild('fahrenheit', $fahrenheit);
$temp->addChild('celsius', $celsius);
// Add the Celsius temperature
$celsius = 28;
$fahrenheit = celsius_to_fahrenheit($celsius);
$temp = $xml->addChild('temperature');
$temp->addChild('celsius', $celsius);
$temp->addChild('fahrenheit', $fahrenheit);
// Output the XML document
echo $xml->asXML();
?>
```
This code will output the following XML document:
```
xml version="1.0"?
82
27.777777777778
28
82.4
```
As you can see, the code converts 82 degrees Fahrenheit to Celsius and 28 degrees Celsius to Fahrenheit, and outputs the results in an XML document.

