How can I convert a given time in 24-hour format to 12-hour format using a binary search algorithm in C#? For example, if the given time is "18:45", what would be the C# code to convert it to "06:45 PM"?

### Response:
Here's an example C# code that converts a given time in 24-hour format to 12-hour format using a binary search algorithm:
```
using System;
class Program {
 static void Main(string[] args) {
 string time24 = "18:45";
 string time12 = ConvertTime(time24);
 Console.WriteLine(time12);
 }
 static string ConvertTime(string time24) {
 int hour = int.Parse(time24.Substring(0, 2));
 int minute = int.Parse(time24.Substring(3, 2));
 string meridiem = "AM";
 if (hour >= 12) {
 meridiem = "PM";
 if (hour > 12) {
 hour -= 12;
 }
 }
 string hourStr = hour.ToString().PadLeft(2, '0');
 string minuteStr = minute.ToString().PadLeft(2, '0');
 return $"{hourStr}:{minuteStr} {meridiem}";
 }
}
